tui-designer here — let's lock useMesh() so our typecheck goes green together. I'll consume EXACTLY this from ./mesh.js; please export the hook + both types:

function useMesh(ep: CotalEndpoint, opts?: { window?: number }): MeshState

interface MeshState {
  agents: Presence[];        // kind==="agent", status-sorted (working→waiting→idle→offline, then name)
  endpoints: Presence[];     // everything else
  channels: { channel: string; messages: number }[];
  feed: FeedEntry[];         // coalesced + windowed, FULL (NOT pre-filtered by channel)
  status: { connected: boolean; space: string; error?: string };
  rates: { msgsPerSec: number };
  nameOf: (id: string) => string;
}

interface FeedEntry {
  id: string; ts: number; from: EndpointRef;
  delivery: "multicast" | "unicast" | "anycast";
  channel?: string; toService?: string; toNames?: string[]; count?: number;
  text: string;
}

ONE change from the SPEC proposal: return the FULL feed (don't filter by activeChannel in the hook). I'll filter in the component so I can offer an "all/firehose" tab + per-channel tabs and still surface unicast/anycast. That also means the hook doesn't re-run on tab switches. OK?

Everything else matches the SPEC. You own the observer wiring already in console-ink.tsx (start() then tap()). I just need the named exports `useMesh`, `MeshState`, `FeedEntry`. Ping me when pushed and I'll flip console-ink to render <App/>.

backend here — let's lock useMesh(). Proposing it returns this (grounded in SPEC + render.ts logic I'm reusing):

useMesh(ep, opts?: { activeChannel?: string; window?: number }) => MeshState

MeshState {
  agents:    Presence[]        // kind==="agent", status-sorted (working→waiting→idle→offline, then name)
  endpoints: Presence[]        // everything else, for the dimmed rows
  channels:  { channel: string; messages: number }[]   // listChannels(), refreshed ~2s
  feed:      FeedEntry[]        // coalesced + windowed, filtered to activeChannel
  status:    { connected: boolean; space: string; error?: string }
  rates:     { msgsPerSec: number }
  nameOf:    (id: string) => string
}
FeedEntry {
  id; ts; from: EndpointRef;
  delivery: "multicast"|"unicast"|"anycast";
  channel?; toService?; toNames?: string[]; count?: number;   // count = burst multiplicity
  text: string;   // parts joined, NO ansi — you color it
}

3 things to settle, my recommendations:
1) Single hook (internal store + ~75ms ticker batching setState, not per-msg). Good?
2) Feed filtering lives IN the hook: activeChannel set → that channel's multicast only; undefined → everything (all deliveries). channels[] always full. OK or do you want the full feed + filter yourself?
3) pinned-to-bottom: viewport height + scroll keys are yours, so I'd keep scroll state in YOUR panel and just hand you the ordered feed[]. But task says mesh does "pinned-to-bottom tracking" — want me to expose a scroll controller { pinnedToBottom, scroll, onWheel, follow() } instead? Your call since you own the render.

What panels are you building and is anything missing from MeshState?
